{
  "texts": [
    "However, this lacks a finer-grained inspection on their process assessment abilities, and the evaluation reliability can be heavily affected by the underlying solution generation model.",
    "Our evaluation includes several open-source PRMs: (1) Math-Shepherd (Wang et al., 2024), which obtains the process label for each step via estimating the empirical probability of this step leading to the correct final answer.",
    "(2) Two LLaMA-3.1-based PRMs from Xiong et al. (2024b), which roughly follow the training methodology of Math-Shepherd but differ in the solution generation models and optimization objectives.",
    "(3) Two Qwen2.5-Math-based PRMs recently released by Skywork (2024).",
    "(4) We also train a PRM by fine-tuning Qwen2.5-Math-7B-Instruct on the PRM800K dataset, namely Qwen2.5-Math-7B-PRM800K."
  ]
}